### Expected behavior

Testing the card in the [Adaptive Card Designer](https://adaptivecards.microsoft.com/designer) gives the expected results:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2620b2cc-d12b-46e7-8454-7a2a98bee491)

The card also works as expected on the web client, Windows and macOS native clients - untested on Android.

### Actual behavior

On the iOS client, several tests fail, and it seems all elements are visible, regardless of the `targetWidth` attribute. Something like this is shown when viewed in the iOS client at different widths:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0596fd0d-f2c0-45d3-861f-f7ac7f2506fd)

### Error details

Tested on iOS:
```
Version: 7.8.1
Build: 7.8.77.2025083603/0513 (general)
Calling Version: 2025.13.01.6
Release Branch: 2025Apr-T2
```

### Type of issue

Feature doesn't work (bug)

